1
00:02:14,200 --> 00:02:19,200
'In a shanty in Mumbai, amidst
different middle class families..'

2
00:02:19,680 --> 00:02:24,320
'..serving others day and night,
sitting beneath the stairs..'

3
00:02:24,400 --> 00:02:27,760
'..the orphaned young man
who was successful in life..'

4
00:02:28,320 --> 00:02:32,120
'This story is about
that innocent Bhola.'

5
00:02:32,200 --> 00:02:34,720
Where has Bhola gone? He is
not to be seen since morning.

6
00:02:34,800 --> 00:02:38,360
I too am searching for Bhola. God
knows where he has gone. - Bhola.

7
00:02:38,440 --> 00:02:40,880
Renu, are you too
searching for Bhola?

8
00:02:41,080 --> 00:02:42,320
Yes, Aunt Leela.

9
00:02:42,400 --> 00:02:44,240
Father has been yelling for
the newspaper since morning.

10
00:02:44,320 --> 00:02:47,280
He says, "I won't drink tea
until I get the newspaper."

11
00:02:47,360 --> 00:02:50,120
What trouble is this! Oh, my God.

12
00:02:50,200 --> 00:02:51,720
Bhola. Bhola.

13
00:02:53,600 --> 00:02:56,520
Where has Bhola gone? It's
time for me to go to tuitions.

14
00:02:56,600 --> 00:02:58,080
He still hasn't
got the shirt ironed.

15
00:02:58,160 --> 00:02:59,560
He has gone to get it.
He will get it soon.

16
00:02:59,640 --> 00:03:01,080
God knows when he will come.

17
00:03:01,160 --> 00:03:02,440
You are harassing me for a shirt.

18
00:03:02,520 --> 00:03:06,520
Bhola has come. Bhola has come.

19
00:03:14,480 --> 00:03:16,800
Aunt. Aunt.

20
00:03:16,880 --> 00:03:19,520
Bhola, you have come.
You got late today.

21
00:03:19,600 --> 00:03:21,080
You left for the market so early.

22
00:03:21,160 --> 00:03:22,240
What to do, Aunt?

23
00:03:22,320 --> 00:03:24,640
Nowadays, market has
become a haggling shop.

24
00:03:24,720 --> 00:03:27,800
It was so crowded. Here is
your grocery. - Give me.

25
00:03:27,880 --> 00:03:30,080
It has chillies
worth Rs.2. And turmeric.

26
00:03:30,160 --> 00:03:31,440
Okay.
- I am in a hurry.

27
00:03:31,680 --> 00:03:33,320
Fine. Go quickly.
- Okay, Aunt.

28
00:03:35,160 --> 00:03:37,720
"I won't eat fish. I
won't eat fish." - Bhola.

29
00:03:38,080 --> 00:03:41,480
Brother, here is your ink.
- Okay.

30
00:03:41,680 --> 00:03:43,080
And here are blank papers.

31
00:03:43,160 --> 00:03:46,680
Bhola, well done. I will
write on these blank papers.

32
00:03:46,880 --> 00:03:50,720
I will write beautiful
scripts and Gemini, B. R. Chopra..

33
00:03:50,800 --> 00:03:52,520
..Vahini, I will
sell it to everybody.

34
00:03:52,600 --> 00:03:55,640
And very soon, I will
become a famous writer. Bhola.

35
00:03:55,720 --> 00:04:00,200
Brother, if I ever
become a producer..

36
00:04:00,280 --> 00:04:02,080
..I will surely buy your story.

37
00:04:02,160 --> 00:04:04,680
But I will first hear it.
- I will surely narrate it.

38
00:04:04,760 --> 00:04:08,320
Sister, here is your
favourite rice. It's old rice.

39
00:04:08,400 --> 00:04:11,480
Bhola, you are so nice.
So good. Bhola.

40
00:04:11,560 --> 00:04:13,080
I will leave now.
- Okay.

41
00:04:13,160 --> 00:04:14,600
Move.
- Okay.

42
00:04:15,880 --> 00:04:19,800
Uncle, you are coughing.
Here is your medicine. Have it.

43
00:04:23,080 --> 00:04:24,200
Bhola.
- Yes.

44
00:04:24,560 --> 00:04:27,840
When is 'Ekadashi' (11th day
of the month)? - I don't know.

45
00:04:28,080 --> 00:04:30,640
When you don't get to eat,
that day is 'Ekadashi'.

46
00:04:30,840 --> 00:04:32,800
For me, 'Ekadashi' comes
three-four times a week.

47
00:04:32,880 --> 00:04:35,400
Shut up. Tell me.
When is 'Ekadashi'?

48
00:04:35,480 --> 00:04:36,640
According to the calendar,
it's tomorrow.

49
00:04:37,080 --> 00:04:38,160
Tomorrow?
- Yes.

50
00:04:38,240 --> 00:04:40,160
Aunt, your grocery.
It has everything.

51
00:04:40,240 --> 00:04:41,320
Even fresh spices.

52
00:04:46,200 --> 00:04:48,400
He is yelling so much.

53
00:04:48,480 --> 00:04:53,280
If he is late for music tuition,
then nobody will hang him.

54
00:04:53,360 --> 00:04:55,320
Where is my shirt?
Where is my shirt?

55
00:04:55,400 --> 00:04:58,480
He is yelling the way Om
Prakash yelled in the movie 'Gopi'.

56
00:04:58,560 --> 00:05:00,640
Sister, why are you yelling?

57
00:05:01,160 --> 00:05:03,160
You always give examples of movies.

58
00:05:03,280 --> 00:05:05,720
Be clear. So that even I
can understand something.

59
00:05:05,800 --> 00:05:06,880
Bhola.
- He has come.

60
00:05:07,000 --> 00:05:09,200
Bhola.
- Yes. - Where is my ironed shirt?

61
00:05:09,280 --> 00:05:11,240
Here is your ironed shirt.

62
00:05:11,320 --> 00:05:13,160
Great.

63
00:05:15,080 --> 00:05:19,360
Great. He thinks that his musical
talent is hidden in his shirt.

64
00:05:19,520 --> 00:05:22,000
The way in 'Bahut Din
Hue' the villain's life..

65
00:05:22,080 --> 00:05:23,320
..dwelled in the parrot.

66
00:05:23,400 --> 00:05:26,400
Sister, again movies..
- Yes. Fine. Let it be. - Fine.

67
00:05:26,560 --> 00:05:31,240
"Ramala, where are you going?"

68
00:05:31,320 --> 00:05:33,120
Bhola. What's the arrival
time of Punjab Mail (train)?

69
00:05:33,200 --> 00:05:34,640
Punjab Mail..

70
00:05:35,280 --> 00:05:37,280
Uncle, who is coming from Punjab?

71
00:05:37,400 --> 00:05:39,440
My daughter, Gauri,
is coming from Agra.

72
00:05:39,640 --> 00:05:44,200
What's the arrival time? - At times,
it's on time. At times, it's late.

73
00:05:44,320 --> 00:05:46,360
But arrival time is 12.20.
- Sure?

74
00:05:46,560 --> 00:05:49,240
You can confirm from the station.

75
00:05:50,080 --> 00:05:54,560
The train from Delhi will
arrive on platform number three.

76
00:05:54,640 --> 00:05:57,080
Bhola, what's
today's college time table?

77
00:05:57,320 --> 00:05:59,200
What do I know? Ask him.

78
00:05:59,320 --> 00:06:02,520
What will he know? He
just knows hotel menus.

79
00:06:02,600 --> 00:06:04,880
Yes. What's the time table?

80
00:06:05,080 --> 00:06:07,800
Physics in the
morning and then Practical.

81
00:06:08,080 --> 00:06:11,760
And in the evening 'Kati
Patang' at the theatre.

82
00:06:12,280 --> 00:06:14,080
"Love.."

83
00:06:14,160 --> 00:06:17,200
Do we go to watch movies everyday?

84
00:06:17,400 --> 00:06:18,520
Who said everyday?

85
00:06:18,600 --> 00:06:22,480
You people watch movies
only seven times a week.

86
00:06:22,560 --> 00:06:23,640
Seven times.
- Move.

87
00:06:23,720 --> 00:06:26,280
Yes. As if you study everyday.

88
00:06:28,880 --> 00:06:32,160
Ms. Renu. Look, what I got for you.

89
00:06:32,280 --> 00:06:34,080
Detective book.

90
00:06:34,880 --> 00:06:37,080
I was searching for
this book since long.

91
00:06:37,160 --> 00:06:38,240
It's good that you brought it.

92
00:06:38,320 --> 00:06:41,400
Renu, I have already read
all these books. - Is that so?

93
00:06:41,480 --> 00:06:43,320
Shall I tell you the story?
- No.

94
00:06:43,400 --> 00:06:44,640
Listen to me. Listen
to me. Listen to me.

95
00:06:44,720 --> 00:06:46,600
There is a fight between
the detective and the hero.

96
00:06:46,880 --> 00:06:50,160
Fight. Detective runs ahead.
The hero follows him.

97
00:06:50,280 --> 00:06:53,360
And they both reach
a 20-storey building.

98
00:06:53,480 --> 00:06:55,000
Don't tell me. I
won't enjoy reading it.

99
00:06:55,080 --> 00:06:57,520
Now, listen. After
reaching the building..

100
00:06:58,120 --> 00:07:00,080
..the detective stands up.

101
00:07:00,600 --> 00:07:04,080
He puts his hand in his pocket.

102
00:07:04,160 --> 00:07:07,240
The hero thinks maybe he is
taking out his cigarette packet.

103
00:07:07,880 --> 00:07:12,720
But no. He pulls out a gun
and not the cigarette packet.

104
00:07:12,800 --> 00:07:15,480
Say pistol. Pistol.

105
00:07:15,560 --> 00:07:16,720
Yes. Pistol.

106
00:07:16,800 --> 00:07:19,240
And then he fires at the hero.

107
00:07:20,720 --> 00:07:22,480
Does my hero die? Tell me quickly.

108
00:07:22,560 --> 00:07:24,560
What happened to my hero?
Does he die? - No, no.

109
00:07:24,640 --> 00:07:27,480
Ms. Renu, all the movies
made here and novels written..

110
00:07:27,560 --> 00:07:29,160
Yes. - Does the hero
die in any of it? - No.

111
00:07:29,240 --> 00:07:32,160
His enemies die. The hero had
emptied the bullets beforehand.

112
00:07:32,240 --> 00:07:34,200
My hero doesn't die. I am fine.

113
00:07:34,280 --> 00:07:35,720
Now, hear the climax.
- Yes.

114
00:07:35,800 --> 00:07:37,080
It's the biggest suspense.

115
00:07:37,160 --> 00:07:41,520
In the swimming pool with a
buffalo.. the hero has a fight.

116
00:07:41,880 --> 00:07:44,080
Don't tell me. I
won't enjoy reading it.

117
00:07:44,160 --> 00:07:46,080
Don't tell me.
- Here is your grocery.

118
00:07:46,800 --> 00:07:48,360
Why did you bring onion?

119
00:07:48,440 --> 00:07:51,640
Because it was cheap. Your
father likes fried onions.

120
00:07:51,720 --> 00:07:55,600
Make it for him.
- Bhola. I want to shave my beard.

121
00:07:55,760 --> 00:07:57,160
Which saloon should I go to?

122
00:07:58,240 --> 00:08:02,440
Is it credit or cash?
- Today, credit.

123
00:08:02,520 --> 00:08:05,160
It's Monday today. All
the shops are close.

124
00:08:05,320 --> 00:08:07,720
I asked a fool.

125
00:08:09,520 --> 00:08:10,720
Bhola, did you bring my cigarette?

126
00:08:11,480 --> 00:08:16,480
Cigarette? Sir.. sir, the
shopkeeper has closed your account.

127
00:08:17,120 --> 00:08:18,400
Then you should have
brought it on your account.

128
00:08:18,480 --> 00:08:19,800
I don't have an account, sir.

129
00:08:19,880 --> 00:08:21,320
What can I do? I want
to use the bathroom.

130
00:08:21,400 --> 00:08:23,280
I have got cigarette for that.

131
00:08:23,360 --> 00:08:25,080
Give it to me. - But it's on
that fatso brother's account.

132
00:08:25,160 --> 00:08:27,800
It's okay. It's okay.
Thanks a ton. Greetings.

133
00:08:27,880 --> 00:08:31,400
"Do come to my village once."

134
00:08:31,480 --> 00:08:34,680
"And when will you be
receptive to my love?"

135
00:08:34,760 --> 00:08:36,640
Bhola. Bhola. Did
you bring my newspaper?

136
00:08:36,720 --> 00:08:39,320
Sorry, Uncle. I forgot to
give you your newspaper.

137
00:08:40,160 --> 00:08:44,480
Fine. Give this
yesterday's newspaper to Dindayal.

138
00:08:44,640 --> 00:08:47,680
He will thank you. You
can have that thanks.

139
00:08:47,880 --> 00:08:49,520
I should take his thanks. Fine.

140
00:08:50,320 --> 00:08:54,000
This is great. Dindayal
pays for the newspaper.

141
00:08:54,080 --> 00:08:56,720
And Makhan Lal reads it.
My work is over.

142
00:08:56,800 --> 00:08:57,880
Let's go to college.

143
00:09:03,000 --> 00:09:07,200
How come my pot is behind?

144
00:09:07,280 --> 00:09:08,360
Ask your pot.

145
00:09:08,600 --> 00:09:13,200
Great. Does my pot have wings
that it will fly on its own.

146
00:09:13,280 --> 00:09:14,640
What do we know?

147
00:09:14,720 --> 00:09:17,480
We just know that we
came here two hours ago.

148
00:09:17,560 --> 00:09:19,560
You came here two hours ago.

149
00:09:19,760 --> 00:09:22,400
And I came in this
shanty ten years ago.

150
00:09:22,680 --> 00:09:24,120
Bear it in mind. Don't forget it.

151
00:09:24,200 --> 00:09:27,520
Great. You are ordering us
the way Shashikala ordered..

152
00:09:27,600 --> 00:09:29,320
..in 'Sirf Paisa Ya Pyar.'

153
00:09:29,400 --> 00:09:31,600
What commotion is this?
Always quarrels.

154
00:09:31,680 --> 00:09:34,800
Come. Come, Prince.
Only you were amiss.

155
00:09:34,880 --> 00:09:36,160
Come down.

156
00:09:36,240 --> 00:09:39,000
Let me tell you that
you can't bully us.

157
00:09:39,080 --> 00:09:41,200
Do I bully you all? - Of course.
What else are you doing?

158
00:09:41,280 --> 00:09:42,360
Get lost.
- Shut up.

159
00:09:42,440 --> 00:09:43,720
Shut up.
- I say keep quiet.

160
00:09:43,800 --> 00:09:45,080
Quiet.
- You keep quiet.

161
00:09:45,160 --> 00:09:46,640
Keep quiet.
- He is coming.

162
00:09:46,720 --> 00:09:47,800
No matter who is coming.
What do we care?

163
00:09:47,880 --> 00:09:50,120
Lorry is here. Sher Singh is coming.

164
00:09:50,200 --> 00:09:51,360
Sher Singh.
- Oh, my God.

165
00:09:51,800 --> 00:09:52,880
Come.

166
00:10:01,880 --> 00:10:03,280
A short while ago,
there was a commotion.

167
00:10:03,400 --> 00:10:04,480
And now, it's so quiet.

168
00:10:04,560 --> 00:10:07,160
Sher Singh is coming.

169
00:10:07,320 --> 00:10:10,120
Sher Singh. He is Sher
Singh and not Dara Singh.

170
00:10:13,720 --> 00:10:16,120
Sher Singh, hello.
- Hello.

171
00:10:26,760 --> 00:10:35,080
Lord, with your blessing,
everything is fine. Thank you.

172
00:10:37,480 --> 00:10:43,080
Bhola, all of them
are fools. Lazy people.

173
00:10:43,440 --> 00:10:45,600
None of them are useful.
Useless, all of them.

174
00:10:46,680 --> 00:10:47,760
Sher Singh.
- Yes.

175
00:10:47,880 --> 00:10:49,680
Nobody is useless in the world.

176
00:10:50,000 --> 00:10:52,400
Some people whose
help we don't take..

177
00:10:52,600 --> 00:10:56,560
..and who are related to us..
they are useless for us.

178
00:10:56,640 --> 00:10:59,600
Now, take my example.
Do you give me any work?

179
00:10:59,680 --> 00:11:02,240
No. - No, right. Doesn't
that make me useless for you?

180
00:11:02,720 --> 00:11:07,440
Bhola. Why has God
given me two hands? - Why?

181
00:11:07,600 --> 00:11:10,880
To do my own work.
Haven't you heard?

182
00:11:11,000 --> 00:11:12,680
Hands are everything.

183
00:11:12,880 --> 00:11:14,720
Mister.
- Yes.

184
00:11:14,800 --> 00:11:17,440
Is there no work in the
world which you can't do?

185
00:11:17,840 --> 00:11:19,680
Mr. Bhola.
- Yes.

186
00:11:19,760 --> 00:11:23,120
There is no work
which a devotee can't do.

187
00:11:23,200 --> 00:11:25,520
Then do one thing.
- Tell me.

188
00:11:25,880 --> 00:11:28,000
The hen which hatches from an egg..

189
00:11:28,080 --> 00:11:30,800
..put the hen back into the egg.
- What?

190
00:11:31,080 --> 00:11:32,360
Yes.
- Hey.

191
00:11:35,000 --> 00:11:36,200
Loafer.

192
00:11:36,280 --> 00:11:38,200
This is the food made with love.
- Food?

193
00:11:38,480 --> 00:11:43,360
Yes. Until you don't
call me loafer, I can't eat.

194
00:11:43,640 --> 00:11:44,720
I can't sleep.

195
00:11:45,160 --> 00:11:51,080
Bhola, don't you ever feel
bad when I call you loafer?

196
00:11:51,320 --> 00:11:52,400
No, Brother.

197
00:11:52,480 --> 00:11:56,280
Even a police officer calls
his child as thief, ruffian.

198
00:11:56,360 --> 00:11:58,200
So, does the child really
become a thief or a ruffian?

199
00:11:58,280 --> 00:11:59,440
Enough. Enough.

200
00:11:59,720 --> 00:12:03,560
Now, you take a break.
And leave. Let me work.

201
00:12:03,640 --> 00:12:07,080
Fine, Brother. You too calm down.

202
00:12:07,160 --> 00:12:11,680
And eat something.

203
00:12:11,760 --> 00:12:16,520
But don't eat too much.
Otherwise, you might fall sick.

204
00:12:16,600 --> 00:12:18,280
Loafer.

205
00:12:19,240 --> 00:12:20,480
Loafer.

206
00:12:25,080 --> 00:12:26,320
What's the matter?

207
00:12:26,400 --> 00:12:30,640
I think he is not
going to college today.

208
00:12:30,720 --> 00:12:33,000
Because he has still not eaten.

209
00:12:33,080 --> 00:12:36,080
What is he eating nowadays?

210
00:12:36,160 --> 00:12:42,800
Fatso, Bhola doesn't
eat meagre meals like us.

211
00:12:43,080 --> 00:12:48,080
He has rich meals day and night.

212
00:12:48,160 --> 00:12:52,520
No. When Bhola goes
with his plate and says..

213
00:12:53,000 --> 00:12:56,600
.."Bhola has come, Bhola
has come", he gets food.

214
00:13:12,480 --> 00:13:15,440
Bhola has come. Bhola has come.

215
00:13:16,520 --> 00:13:18,880
The lunch is still not ready.
It will take some time.

216
00:13:19,000 --> 00:13:20,840
Aunt, I will be late for my college.

217
00:13:21,080 --> 00:13:23,640
So, what should I do?
Always cook for you?

218
00:13:23,720 --> 00:13:25,280
Not always, Aunt. At times.

219
00:13:25,480 --> 00:13:27,800
You are hungry and still
you are acting smugly.

220
00:13:27,880 --> 00:13:30,640
If you are so hungry,
then eat grass.

221
00:13:30,720 --> 00:13:34,640
Aunt, I remembered
you wanted kerosene.

222
00:13:34,880 --> 00:13:37,000
Take out the container. I
will bring it in the evening.

223
00:13:37,080 --> 00:13:39,200
If not you, then will
I bring the kerosene.

224
00:13:50,720 --> 00:13:53,200
Bhola has come. Bhola has come.

225
00:13:53,400 --> 00:13:54,560
Bhola has come.

226
00:13:54,880 --> 00:13:57,280
Everyday you are here. You
are not talking anything new.

227
00:13:57,640 --> 00:14:01,240
Mr. Anand, aunt must have
understood what I meant.

228
00:14:01,320 --> 00:14:02,720
She must have understood.

229
00:14:03,080 --> 00:14:05,240
Why don't you clearly say
that I have come to beg?

230
00:14:05,400 --> 00:14:06,480
Mr. Anand.

231
00:14:06,560 --> 00:14:09,680
Why don't you beg and say
"Give me something to eat?"

232
00:14:09,880 --> 00:14:14,160
I am hungry. You act proud.
And you beg.

233
00:14:14,760 --> 00:14:17,800
What did you say? Say it again.

234
00:14:18,280 --> 00:14:21,880
If you say that again,
then I will not spare you.

235
00:14:23,080 --> 00:14:25,000
Nobody does a favour to Bhola..

236
00:14:25,080 --> 00:14:26,200
..by giving him meals.

237
00:14:26,800 --> 00:14:28,760
He serves everybody diligently.

238
00:14:29,880 --> 00:14:33,120
He studies in college.
He passes with good marks.

239
00:14:33,320 --> 00:14:34,400
He receives scholarship.

240
00:14:34,560 --> 00:14:38,080
He is not indebted to anybody.
But we are indebted to him.

241
00:14:38,160 --> 00:14:40,760
You should learn from him.

242
00:14:43,080 --> 00:14:46,120
Anand's mother. Bhola has come.

243
