746
00:44:32,680 --> 00:44:35,440
Don't worry. Bhola's
love will be eternal.

747
00:44:35,520 --> 00:44:39,320
Bhola's love will be eternal.
Bhola's love will be eternal.

748
00:44:39,400 --> 00:44:40,880
Bhola will be in the hospital.

749
00:44:41,560 --> 00:44:44,400
How to love her?
Very difficult question.

750
00:44:45,640 --> 00:44:47,080
Take the help of the book.

751
00:44:48,280 --> 00:44:52,120
Lovers are beaten. Oh, my God.

752
00:44:52,800 --> 00:44:53,880
Another book..

753
00:44:54,880 --> 00:44:58,120
Heartaches. Before loving. No.

754
00:44:59,000 --> 00:45:02,240
What to do? I will
have to love Gauri.

755
00:45:02,640 --> 00:45:05,120
How to talk to her?
How to call her outside?

756
00:45:07,120 --> 00:45:10,320
Idea. I will tease her
and she will come outside.

757
00:45:28,480 --> 00:45:31,520
"Mad girl has left the house."

758
00:45:31,600 --> 00:45:33,520
"Like a flower."

759
00:45:33,840 --> 00:45:36,200
"Biting her finger,
she has gone wild.."

760
00:45:36,280 --> 00:45:37,600
"Mad girl."

761
00:45:37,880 --> 00:45:39,560
What did you say?
- Nothing. Nothing.

762
00:45:39,640 --> 00:45:44,600
No. No. No.

763
00:45:44,680 --> 00:45:48,400
Listen. Listen. Oh, my God.
Oh, my God. Listen.

764
00:45:48,480 --> 00:45:50,360
What did you say?
- Nothing.

765
00:45:50,440 --> 00:45:51,520
Why did you sing that song?

766
00:45:51,600 --> 00:45:53,600
Just like that. I am
telling the truth.

767
00:45:53,680 --> 00:45:55,520
I didn't sing that
song to tease you.

768
00:45:55,640 --> 00:45:57,400
I sang that song to call you out.

769
00:46:01,320 --> 00:46:02,560
Now, say.
- Why are you scared of me?

770
00:46:02,640 --> 00:46:04,800
What are you doing?
Look, the well is here.

771
00:46:05,000 --> 00:46:07,080
If I fell down then I will die.

772
00:46:07,200 --> 00:46:08,880
Bhola will be down.
And bubbles will come up.

773
00:46:09,600 --> 00:46:10,680
Brother.

774
00:46:11,400 --> 00:46:13,000
Why do you get
scared when you see me?

775
00:46:13,080 --> 00:46:14,160
The way a mouse is
afraid of the cat.

776
00:46:14,680 --> 00:46:16,640
Don't you pity me?

777
00:46:16,720 --> 00:46:22,520
Yes. Nowadays, I pity you a bit.
Earlier, I was really scared.

778
00:46:22,680 --> 00:46:25,600
But now, my fear is reducing.

779
00:46:25,680 --> 00:46:27,400
And my heart says to talk to you.

780
00:46:28,080 --> 00:46:30,200
Gauri, why are you quiet?

781
00:46:31,520 --> 00:46:34,280
If I say something,
people say that I am mad.

782
00:46:34,360 --> 00:46:35,480
Then you keep quiet.

783
00:46:36,080 --> 00:46:38,240
When I keep quiet, still
people say that I am mad.

784
00:46:38,320 --> 00:46:40,480
Then say something. Talk.

785
00:46:40,560 --> 00:46:42,080
Otherwise, nothing will happen.

786
00:46:42,160 --> 00:46:44,800
You talk and I will talk.
- What should I say?

787
00:46:45,200 --> 00:46:48,640
Anything. About your life,
about your childhood.

788
00:46:50,240 --> 00:46:52,320
What do I say about my life?

789
00:46:53,120 --> 00:46:56,000
I can only say that it
would have been better..

790
00:46:56,080 --> 00:46:58,800
..if I had not been born.

791
00:46:59,600 --> 00:47:02,760
No. You shouldn't say that.

792
00:47:03,880 --> 00:47:07,840
Gauri, if I ask you something,
will you feel bad?

793
00:47:08,600 --> 00:47:12,160
No, Bhola. Why will I feel
bad if you say something good?

794
00:47:12,760 --> 00:47:16,080
Nobody talks properly to me.

795
00:47:16,200 --> 00:47:18,080
But you talk sweetly.

796
00:47:18,360 --> 00:47:20,640
But that day, I
mean with Mr. Jeevan..

797
00:47:20,720 --> 00:47:23,560
..on the engagement day,
your ferocious form..

798
00:47:23,640 --> 00:47:25,440
Throwing vessels.

799
00:47:25,520 --> 00:47:28,640
If somebody calls a girl
mad and asks for Rs.15000..

800
00:47:28,720 --> 00:47:30,240
..in front of
everybody humiliates her..

801
00:47:30,320 --> 00:47:32,760
..then forget me,
any girl will do this.

802
00:47:32,880 --> 00:47:36,480
Gauri, you throw vessels on others.

803
00:47:36,720 --> 00:47:38,400
So, they call you mad.

804
00:47:38,880 --> 00:47:42,080
They call you mad, so,
you throw vessels at them.

805
00:47:42,240 --> 00:47:45,200
There is a problem.
There is only one solution.

806
00:47:45,520 --> 00:47:49,080
Not to get angry. And
think about harmony.

807
00:47:49,240 --> 00:47:53,160
I mean like other girls,
behave politely.

808
00:47:54,080 --> 00:47:57,360
What do I know how
other girls behave?

809
00:47:57,880 --> 00:47:59,680
I was in the mental
asylum for ten years.

810
00:47:59,880 --> 00:48:01,800
What do I know how
the outside world is?

811
00:48:02,280 --> 00:48:05,080
I just know that now I am not mad.

812
00:48:05,160 --> 00:48:06,880
People living here are mad.

813
00:48:07,400 --> 00:48:09,640
Somebody is crazy for music,
somebody for movies.

814
00:48:09,880 --> 00:48:11,000
Somebody is crazy for clothes..

815
00:48:11,080 --> 00:48:12,240
..somebody for jewellery.

816
00:48:12,320 --> 00:48:13,720
And everybody is crazy for money.

817
00:48:14,200 --> 00:48:15,280
They all might be mad.

818
00:48:15,640 --> 00:48:20,440
That doesn't mean that they
can call me mad all the time.

819
00:48:21,560 --> 00:48:27,520
Gauri. Gauri, don't cry. I
can't see anybody crying.

820
00:48:28,000 --> 00:48:30,120
I too can't endure this injustice.

821
00:48:31,000 --> 00:48:34,560
Till date, nobody consoled me.

822
00:48:35,480 --> 00:48:37,000
Bhola, you will talk
to me considering me..

823
00:48:37,080 --> 00:48:39,320
..to be a nice girl, won't you?

824
00:48:39,480 --> 00:48:43,200
Will I? I will have to do it.
I will have to talk a lot.

825
00:48:43,480 --> 00:48:46,080
Otherwise, how will my plan succeed?

826
00:48:46,160 --> 00:48:48,080
Plan? What plan?
- Nothing. Nothing.

827
00:48:49,160 --> 00:48:50,240
What is this, Bhola?

828
00:48:50,320 --> 00:48:53,080
Just now you were saying
that we will talk a lot.

829
00:48:53,200 --> 00:48:55,120
And now, you have
become so quiet. Why?

830
00:48:56,000 --> 00:48:58,080
Gauri, there is a problem.

831
00:48:58,560 --> 00:49:00,520
A lot of families
live in this shanty.

832
00:49:00,600 --> 00:49:02,480
How will we talk alone?

833
00:49:02,680 --> 00:49:05,480
Why? You call me and I will come.
- But how?

834
00:49:05,720 --> 00:49:07,600
How did you call me just now?
- By singing.

835
00:49:07,840 --> 00:49:09,520
So sing.
- Okay.

836
00:49:09,600 --> 00:49:10,760
"Mad girl."

837
00:49:10,840 --> 00:49:13,800
I told you to call me and
you are calling the mad girl.

838
00:49:14,320 --> 00:49:17,080
Sorry. But which other song to sing?

839
00:49:17,360 --> 00:49:22,120
"My songs are calling you."

840
00:49:22,200 --> 00:49:24,360
"My songs."

841
00:49:24,440 --> 00:49:28,400
"My beloved."

842
00:49:28,480 --> 00:49:29,880
Did you hear this song?
- Yes.

843
00:49:30,160 --> 00:49:32,080
We will sing this song.
- Okay.

844
00:49:32,200 --> 00:49:33,440
The work is done.

845
00:49:33,720 --> 00:49:37,160
I will sing this song when I
want to talk to you. And you come.

846
00:49:37,560 --> 00:49:40,280
If you sing melodiously,
I will definitely come.

847
00:49:41,200 --> 00:49:42,880
Gauri.

848
00:49:43,640 --> 00:49:45,280
Your mother is calling you?
- Yes.

849
00:49:45,480 --> 00:49:46,560
Mother.

850
00:49:48,000 --> 00:49:51,480
Gauri. Where have you gone?

851
00:49:53,720 --> 00:49:56,080
Gauri. Gauri.

852
00:49:56,160 --> 00:49:57,240
Move.

853
00:49:57,320 --> 00:50:00,400
Aunt, Gauri is not here.
Greetings, Aunt. How are you?

854
00:50:00,480 --> 00:50:01,560
Are you fine?

855
00:50:01,640 --> 00:50:04,480
Why are you being worried
about me all of a sudden?

856
00:50:04,560 --> 00:50:08,160
Aunt, you look so thin.
Are you not well?

857
00:50:08,240 --> 00:50:10,000
What nonsense!

858
00:50:10,080 --> 00:50:12,080
I am not talking nonsense. I
am swaying the wraparound.

859
00:50:12,320 --> 00:50:15,800
What. - No, no. I am washing..
no, drying the wraparound.

860
00:50:16,080 --> 00:50:19,080
Do you have to talk for that?

861
00:50:19,280 --> 00:50:22,800
Yes, Aunt. If we talk, we exhale.
It dries the wraparound.

862
00:50:22,880 --> 00:50:24,400
Sari. Sari.

863
00:50:24,480 --> 00:50:26,160
Why are you harping about sari?

864
00:50:26,240 --> 00:50:28,880
Aunt, I was saying that a sari
can be made with this wraparound.

865
00:50:29,520 --> 00:50:31,000
Why are you dancing?

866
00:50:31,080 --> 00:50:32,560
Because you are making me dance.

867
00:50:33,600 --> 00:50:35,720
Gauri. God knows where she has gone.

868
00:50:35,800 --> 00:50:38,160
So many times I told her
not to leave the house.

869
00:50:38,320 --> 00:50:39,480
Still she doesn't heed me.

870
00:50:39,680 --> 00:50:43,080
Aunt, she didn't come here.
- Then where did she go?

871
00:50:43,160 --> 00:50:45,480
She must be inside. She must
be inside. Inside. Inside.

872
00:50:45,560 --> 00:50:48,240
I checked inside. She is not there.

873
00:50:48,320 --> 00:50:51,400
You checked inside.
So, have I hidden her?

874
00:50:51,480 --> 00:50:53,280
Is she hidden here?
Go and check inside.

875
00:50:53,360 --> 00:50:55,240
Fine. I will check inside.
- Go.

876
00:50:56,520 --> 00:50:58,200
Saved.

877
00:50:59,080 --> 00:51:01,800
Bhola has come. Bhola has come.

878
00:51:03,080 --> 00:51:05,080
Bhola, you want food?

879
00:51:06,160 --> 00:51:09,200
Don't you know that
it's 'Ekadashi' today?

880
00:51:09,280 --> 00:51:10,800
It's our fast. I have not cooked.

881
00:51:13,080 --> 00:51:14,160
Fine.

882
00:51:18,800 --> 00:51:21,480
Brother.
- Come.

883
00:51:22,560 --> 00:51:23,640
Brother.
- Yes.

884
00:51:23,720 --> 00:51:25,320
You didn't drive the lorry today.

885
00:51:25,400 --> 00:51:30,800
Look, Bhola. In a week, one day
is an off for me and the lorry.

886
00:51:31,480 --> 00:51:33,520
That's why you are exercising.

887
00:51:34,320 --> 00:51:37,360
Brother, I have heard of water
proof and shock proof watch.

888
00:51:37,440 --> 00:51:39,440
But this is the first time that I
am seeing an exercise proof watch.

889
00:51:40,080 --> 00:51:41,520
Loafer.

890
00:51:44,560 --> 00:51:48,720
Bhola, I had a nice friend.

891
00:51:48,880 --> 00:51:50,800
Friend? Like me?
- Yes.

892
00:51:51,520 --> 00:51:54,120
But he died.
- And I am alive.

893
00:51:54,360 --> 00:51:57,320
Bhola, I like three
things in the world.

894
00:51:57,880 --> 00:51:59,520
My mother.
- Mother?

895
00:51:59,640 --> 00:52:03,200
My mom. Second is my
friend's memento. This watch.

896
00:52:03,400 --> 00:52:06,080
And third one?
- Third is my mind.

897
00:52:08,200 --> 00:52:13,320
Bhola, I am a Sardar (Sikh).
My mind is as I am.

898
00:52:13,640 --> 00:52:16,160
Brother, shall I clean your room?

899
00:52:16,240 --> 00:52:19,480
Why? Your sister-in-law
won't come to stay here.

900
00:52:19,640 --> 00:52:22,080
I have come alone.
And I will die alone.

901
00:52:22,160 --> 00:52:24,320
Why do you talk of dying?

902
00:52:24,400 --> 00:52:27,160
First, eat, live and then dye.

903
00:52:27,400 --> 00:52:29,480
I remembered. Brother,
did you have your lunch?

904
00:52:29,560 --> 00:52:30,640
Can't you see?

905
00:52:30,720 --> 00:52:33,720
I have still not taken a bath. I
have not prayed. How can I eat?

906
00:52:34,400 --> 00:52:38,080
You are right. Brother, I
asked whether you had your meal.

907
00:52:38,160 --> 00:52:40,080
But you didn't ask me.

908
00:52:40,480 --> 00:52:42,360
Bhola, did you eat?

909
00:52:45,080 --> 00:52:48,160
Bhola has come. Bhola has come.

910
00:52:48,720 --> 00:52:51,000
You have still not eaten.

911
00:52:53,720 --> 00:52:55,120
Have a banana.

912
00:52:55,640 --> 00:52:57,640
No, Brother. I won't take it.

913
00:52:58,000 --> 00:52:59,240
I will take it only when
somebody gives it to me.

914
00:52:59,320 --> 00:53:02,280
Fine. Fine. I will give it to you.

915
00:53:05,720 --> 00:53:06,800
Here.

916
00:53:06,880 --> 00:53:08,080
You are feeding me for free?

917
00:53:08,160 --> 00:53:11,480
No. I am giving it to you lovingly.
Fruits are sweet.

918
00:53:11,880 --> 00:53:14,880
I don't want sweet fruits.
I want hard earned fruits.

919
00:53:15,080 --> 00:53:16,880
First, give me some
work and then reward.

920
00:53:17,360 --> 00:53:20,400
I remembered. Go bring
the round thing. - What?

921
00:53:20,480 --> 00:53:21,560
The tyre.

922
00:53:21,640 --> 00:53:23,480
So, say that. Here.

923
00:53:27,000 --> 00:53:29,360
Now, what?
- Keep this tyre back there.

924
00:53:30,400 --> 00:53:31,480
Keep it.

925
00:53:33,720 --> 00:53:36,440
You said to give you some work.

926
00:53:36,600 --> 00:53:39,280
You would have done the work.
Here is your fruit.

927
00:53:39,520 --> 00:53:40,880
All of it?
- Yes.

928
00:53:41,000 --> 00:53:42,640
And you?
- God is there for me.

929
00:53:42,720 --> 00:53:44,280
That is fine. But.. -Look.

930
00:53:44,640 --> 00:53:48,080
Leave. If I get angry,
I will slap you.

931
00:53:48,160 --> 00:53:49,240
Greetings.
- Who is it?

932
00:53:49,320 --> 00:53:50,400
Nobody.

933
00:53:51,480 --> 00:53:52,560
Naughty.

934
00:54:05,000 --> 00:54:06,080
Renu.

935
00:54:06,720 --> 00:54:08,280
Banana.
- It's not pumpkin.

936
00:54:08,360 --> 00:54:11,240
Such delicious fruits. I was
wondering what to prepare for lunch.

937
00:54:11,320 --> 00:54:14,400
I will eat bananas. You
have come at the right time.

938
00:54:14,480 --> 00:54:15,560
Renu, listen to me.

939
00:54:15,640 --> 00:54:17,120
Father. Father.
- Renu. Renu.

940
00:54:17,200 --> 00:54:20,360
Father, look. Bhola
has got this for me.

941
00:54:20,480 --> 00:54:23,800
You too eat. Here. Brother.

942
00:54:24,000 --> 00:54:25,640
Brother, such delicious fruits.

943
00:54:25,720 --> 00:54:27,640
If you eat two, you don't have to
eat anything else for breakfast.

944
00:54:27,720 --> 00:54:30,000
Give me four. So that I
don't have to eat lunch too.

945
00:54:30,320 --> 00:54:32,080
Two benefits.
My appetite will be full.

946
00:54:32,160 --> 00:54:33,720
And I won't have to
eat food cooked by you.

947
00:54:33,800 --> 00:54:34,880
Here.

948
00:54:36,320 --> 00:54:38,360
Bhola, you are so nice.

949
00:54:42,000 --> 00:54:44,560
These fruits are sweet
like your conversations.

950
00:54:45,720 --> 00:54:48,280
Bhola, do one thing.
- I understood.

951
00:54:48,800 --> 00:54:51,520
I will wash the plate and I
will drink water and go to sleep.

952
00:54:55,400 --> 00:54:58,760
Bhola. Did you read
today's newspaper?

953
00:54:59,360 --> 00:55:05,520
Did you hear? In our
city 4424 people starve.

954
00:55:06,000 --> 00:55:11,560
Its wrong, Uncle.
Not 4424. In fact 4425.

955
00:55:12,880 --> 00:55:14,200
Today I too will starve.

956
00:55:27,000 --> 00:55:29,000
I had kept the watch here.
Where did it go?

957
00:55:31,000 --> 00:55:34,160
Where are the silver glasses?
I kept it here.

958
00:55:34,400 --> 00:55:37,120
Brother. Brother.
- Why are you yelling?

959
00:55:37,200 --> 00:55:39,000
Two silver glasses have vanished.

960
00:55:39,080 --> 00:55:40,640
Has there ever been
robbery in this house?

961
00:55:40,720 --> 00:55:43,120
Why are you staring at me?
Two silver glasses.

962
00:55:43,200 --> 00:55:45,560
Oh, God. Why are you yelling?

963
00:55:45,640 --> 00:55:48,560
Its only two glasses. Search
properly. You will find them.

964
00:55:48,640 --> 00:55:53,240
How? Not one, but two glasses.
Silver glasses.

965
00:55:54,160 --> 00:55:56,640
Father. Father. Robbery.

966
00:55:56,720 --> 00:55:59,280
Two silver glasses got
robbed in broad daylight.

967
00:55:59,640 --> 00:56:01,160
Really, dear?
- Yes, Father.

968
00:56:02,560 --> 00:56:04,760
The world is really bad.
- Two glasses.

969
00:56:04,840 --> 00:56:07,520
But dear, which newspaper
has this news appeared in?

970
00:56:07,600 --> 00:56:10,720
I didn't see it in this.
- Oh, my God.

971
00:56:11,000 --> 00:56:13,720
My silver glasses. Where
should I go? Who shall I ask?

972
00:56:13,800 --> 00:56:16,760
Sher Singh. Sher Singh, two
silver glasses got stolen.

973
00:56:17,000 --> 00:56:18,520
Look, robbery was
committed in our house today.

974
00:56:18,600 --> 00:56:20,000
Tomorrow, it could be your house.

975
00:56:20,080 --> 00:56:22,520
Even my watch has been stolen.

976
00:56:23,000 --> 00:56:25,320
Stolen? Then why are you quiet?

977
00:56:25,400 --> 00:56:27,800
Why are you yelling? The
thief is from this shanty.

978
00:56:27,880 --> 00:56:29,320
Then why are you pointing at me?

979
00:56:29,400 --> 00:56:32,320
Will I steal in my house?
- I will nab the thief.

980
00:56:32,400 --> 00:56:35,320
When? Two silver glasses.

981
00:56:35,400 --> 00:56:37,720
Its silver glasses. Do you
know how expensive silver is..

982
00:56:37,800 --> 00:56:40,800
Keep quiet. Harping about
silver glasses. Go inside.

983
00:56:48,400 --> 00:56:51,200
Bhola. Bhola.

984
00:56:52,440 --> 00:56:54,000
Today, you had copied
all the English notes..

985
00:56:54,080 --> 00:56:55,160
..in the classroom, hadn't you?

986
00:56:55,280 --> 00:56:56,640
Copy it for me too.

987
00:56:57,480 --> 00:57:00,400
You don't get up. Get up.

988
00:57:03,000 --> 00:57:04,080
Bhola has vanished.

989
00:57:07,800 --> 00:57:08,880
I don't understand.

990
00:57:09,200 --> 00:57:11,240
No film company accepts my story.

991
00:57:11,480 --> 00:57:13,040
I send it today, and tomorrow,
I get it back.

992
00:57:13,800 --> 00:57:14,880
No problem.

993
00:57:15,000 --> 00:57:17,720
Tomorrow, I will send all my
stories to foreign country.

994
00:57:17,800 --> 00:57:20,000
MGM. Columbia. Paramount.

995
00:57:20,120 --> 00:57:21,720
Sir.
- Paramount has come.

996
00:57:21,800 --> 00:57:23,320
No, sir. Postman.
- Postman.

997
00:57:24,760 --> 00:57:29,000
Coming. Postman.
Again a return script.

998
00:57:29,480 --> 00:57:33,000
Look, postman. I am
afraid of only you.

999
00:57:33,080 --> 00:57:35,000
Because you always
bring my scripts back.

1000
00:57:35,080 --> 00:57:38,000
But sir, this time I didn't
bring your story back. - Then?

1001
00:57:38,080 --> 00:57:39,760
I have got a money order for you.
- Money order?

1002
00:57:39,840 --> 00:57:41,360
Yes. Look, Rs.60.
- Wow.

1003
00:57:41,640 --> 00:57:43,000
And in the next month, your story..

1004
00:57:43,080 --> 00:57:45,480
..will be printed in film magazine.

1005
00:57:45,640 --> 00:57:47,000
What are you saying?
- Yes, sir.

1006
00:57:47,080 --> 00:57:48,160
Really?
- Yes.

1007
00:57:48,240 --> 00:57:52,000
Yes. I had written to the
publisher saying if you don't..

1008
00:57:52,080 --> 00:57:55,200
..print this story then I
will send many stories to you.

1009
00:57:55,360 --> 00:57:56,720
Now, they will print it out of fear.

1010
00:57:56,800 --> 00:57:58,720
Yes, sir. Sign here.

1011
00:57:59,000 --> 00:58:00,080
I will have to sign?
- Yes.

1012
00:58:00,160 --> 00:58:02,760
I have never signed. I will sign.

1013
00:58:04,000 --> 00:58:05,080
Hold this.

1014
00:58:05,160 --> 00:58:06,240
Sumitra.
- Sir.

1015
00:58:06,320 --> 00:58:08,360
Leave.
- Sir, take your money.

1016
00:58:08,560 --> 00:58:11,120
It's 60.
- Yes, sir. - Fine? - Yes.

1017
00:58:11,200 --> 00:58:12,280
Sumitra.

1018
00:58:13,080 --> 00:58:14,720
Sumitra.
- What happened?

1019
00:58:17,720 --> 00:58:18,800
Why are you laughing?

1020
00:58:18,880 --> 00:58:21,000
Sumitra, my story is going
to be printed in the magazine.

1021
00:58:21,080 --> 00:58:24,000
Look, 60.. No, I have
received a money order of Rs.50.

1022
00:58:24,400 --> 00:58:26,280
Can't you see that I
am grinding the spices?

1023
00:58:26,360 --> 00:58:27,440
Keep it on the table.

1024
00:58:32,000 --> 00:58:36,880
Chatterjee. Bring the
ink and blank paper.

1025
00:58:37,000 --> 00:58:39,720
And go on writing,
writing and writing.

1026
00:58:43,760 --> 00:58:45,400
Sister-in-law, I
have brought grocery.

1027
00:58:45,720 --> 00:58:48,240
Bhola, I am working.
Keep it on the table.

1028
00:59:07,400 --> 00:59:08,640
Where's Rs.50?

1029
00:59:13,320 --> 00:59:15,000
Just now, Bhola brought the grocery.

1030
00:59:28,720 --> 00:59:31,000
Bhola. Bhola, you
brought the grocery..

1031
00:59:31,080 --> 00:59:33,560
..and kept it on the table, right?

1032
00:59:34,000 --> 00:59:35,880
Yes, Sister-in-law.
What's the matter?

1033
00:59:36,000 --> 00:59:39,760
Rs.50 were kept on
the table. Where is it?

1034
00:59:42,000 --> 00:59:43,880
Sister-in-law, I don't know.

1035
00:59:44,000 --> 00:59:45,760
If you won't know,
then who else will know?

1036
00:59:46,000 --> 00:59:47,880
Besides you, nobody
else comes to our house.

1037
00:59:48,000 --> 00:59:51,040
Brother, I swear. I don't
know who took the money.

1038
00:59:51,120 --> 00:59:52,720
How did it vanish?

1039
00:59:53,000 --> 00:59:54,200
There was a
robbery in our house too.

1040
00:59:54,280 --> 00:59:55,520
Somebody stole my nose ring.

1041
00:59:55,600 --> 00:59:58,640
Everybody is being
robbed in the shanty.

1042
00:59:58,720 --> 01:00:01,440
My two silver glasses got robbed.

1043
01:00:01,720 --> 01:00:04,160
And Anand's gold chain too.

1044
01:00:04,400 --> 01:00:06,720
Oh, my God. That's really bad.

1045
01:00:07,080 --> 01:00:08,800
It means the thief
is not an outsider.

1046
01:00:08,880 --> 01:00:11,720
Yes. But he doesn't
come in our grasp.

1047
01:00:11,800 --> 01:00:14,240
We all knew. But we didn't say.

1048
01:00:14,800 --> 01:00:16,280
But now, we won't keep quiet.

1049
01:00:16,360 --> 01:00:18,800
You came in the house. And
silver glasses disappeared.

1050
01:00:18,880 --> 01:00:20,440
Not one, but two.

1051
01:00:20,600 --> 01:00:23,120
You had come to eat and
you took the gold chain.

1052
01:00:23,600 --> 01:00:25,520
It's futile to sit quiet.

1053
01:00:25,600 --> 01:00:28,720
Will somebody do something?
- Yes.

1054
01:00:28,800 --> 01:00:31,000
Bhola, what are they all saying?

1055
01:00:31,160 --> 01:00:32,240
Uncle, I don't know.

1056
01:00:32,320 --> 01:00:34,000
Where are you going?

1057
01:00:34,440 --> 01:00:36,520
Uncle, you are the eldest here.

1058
01:00:36,720 --> 01:00:39,360
You ask him. Renu's silver glasses.

1059
01:00:39,440 --> 01:00:41,520
Aunt's nose ring.
Anand's gold chain.

1060
01:00:41,600 --> 01:00:44,080
And her Rs.50 kept on the table.

1061
01:00:44,240 --> 01:00:46,080
Where did it all go?
Where did it all go?

1062
01:00:46,280 --> 01:00:49,000
Yes. You forgot brother's watch.

1063
01:00:51,720 --> 01:00:54,280
Great. Even after hearing
everything, he walked away.

1064
01:00:54,360 --> 01:00:56,080
You tell me what does this mean?

1065
01:00:56,400 --> 01:00:59,800
It's futile to talk. He
will answer to only beatings.

1066
01:01:00,120 --> 01:01:01,600
You people search his belonging.

1067
01:01:01,680 --> 01:01:04,400
Maybe he hid things there.
I will frisk him.

1068
01:01:04,480 --> 01:01:06,400
Jeevan. Jeevan, listen to me.

1069
01:01:06,480 --> 01:01:09,000
Shut up. Take out
whatever you have. Come on.

1070
01:01:09,080 --> 01:01:11,560
Mohan, listen to me. - You
frisk him. Listen to me. - Come on.

1071
01:01:11,720 --> 01:01:14,880
Listen to me.
- Found it. Money. - Oh, my God.

1072
01:01:15,000 --> 01:01:18,000
1, 2, 3, 4, 5. 50. Remember.

1073
01:01:18,080 --> 01:01:20,080
A thief can't hide for long.
Someday, he gets caught.

1074
01:01:20,520 --> 01:01:22,880
Tell me. How did you get this money?

1075
01:01:23,280 --> 01:01:26,120
Just now, you said
that you didn't steal.

1076
01:01:26,200 --> 01:01:31,320
Earlier you were blabbering.
Now, what happened?

1077
01:01:31,400 --> 01:01:32,480
Speak up.

1078
01:01:32,640 --> 01:01:35,160
I am telling the truth.
I am not a thief.

1079
01:01:35,240 --> 01:01:37,480
How did you get Rs.50 then?

1080
01:01:37,560 --> 01:01:39,720
It's my hard earned money.

1081
01:01:39,800 --> 01:01:43,320
What did you do? How did you
earn this? Tell me. Speak up.

1082
01:01:43,560 --> 01:01:47,200
I.. No, no.

1083
01:01:48,160 --> 01:01:51,200
Look. How he is staring like an owl.

1084
01:01:51,280 --> 01:01:54,240
He won't speak like this.
Only beatings will do the trick.

1085
01:01:54,320 --> 01:01:57,160
Am I right?
- Don't beat me.

1086
01:01:57,400 --> 01:02:00,280
I kept the money in my
pocket so that I don't lose it.

1087
01:02:00,360 --> 01:02:03,400
Chanting God's name and stealing.

1088
01:02:03,480 --> 01:02:05,560
By keeping the money in the pocket,
will it belong to you?

1089
01:02:05,640 --> 01:02:09,000
I see. Now, I know where
you disappeared at night.

1090
01:02:09,080 --> 01:02:11,080
So, he didn't sleep here at night.

1091
01:02:11,160 --> 01:02:13,800
He sells the goods
he steals at night.

1092
01:02:13,880 --> 01:02:15,440
And in the morning, he
quietly comes and sleeps.

1093
01:02:16,080 --> 01:02:18,360
No, no. It's not true.

1094
01:02:18,720 --> 01:02:22,720
I earned it to pay
my examination fees.

1095
01:02:23,400 --> 01:02:25,080
Look at his face.

1096
01:02:25,160 --> 01:02:28,080
Sister-in-law, give me my money.
- What money?

1097
01:02:28,160 --> 01:02:29,560
It's my hard earned money.

1098
01:02:29,640 --> 01:02:32,600
No. It's the money you robbed.

1099
01:02:32,680 --> 01:02:34,560
Sister-in-law. Sister-in-law.
- Beat him. Beat him.

1100
01:02:34,640 --> 01:02:38,200
No. No. No.
- Stop. Stop.

1101
01:02:38,280 --> 01:02:40,720
Don't beat him. We will take him
to the police station. Come on.

1102
01:02:40,800 --> 01:02:43,400
What commotion is going on?

1103
01:02:44,120 --> 01:02:49,080
Brother. Brother.. I am not a thief.

1104
01:02:49,280 --> 01:02:52,640
Who says that you are a thief?
You can't be a thief, Bhola.

1105
01:02:52,720 --> 01:02:55,000
Everybody in the shanty
knows that he is the thief.

1106
01:02:55,080 --> 01:02:57,080
Your saying is of no avail.

1107
01:02:57,240 --> 01:03:00,720
Shut up. Talking nonsense.

1108
01:03:01,360 --> 01:03:03,000
If fools call a swan a crow..

1109
01:03:03,080 --> 01:03:04,880
..then will it become a crow?

1110
01:03:05,000 --> 01:03:07,000
Is he your relative?
- What?

1111
01:03:07,080 --> 01:03:09,000
Only beatings will
reform him. Beat him.

1112
01:03:09,080 --> 01:03:14,280
Stop. If anybody raises hands
on Bhola, I won't spare him.

1113
01:03:14,360 --> 01:03:15,480
Leave.

1114
01:03:15,560 --> 01:03:19,280
Why should we leave? - You
won't leave? I will deal with you.

1115
01:03:25,000 --> 01:03:26,640
Bhola, don't worry.

1116
01:03:27,000 --> 01:03:30,800
If anybody says
anything to you, just call me.

1117
01:03:30,880 --> 01:03:32,840
I will not spare them. Got it?

1118
01:03:37,600 --> 01:03:38,680
Uncle.

1119
01:03:40,720 --> 01:03:41,800
Uncle.

1120
01:03:42,720 --> 01:03:44,000
Why are you looking at me like this?

1121
01:03:44,800 --> 01:03:47,240
Like others, you too
think that I am a thief?

1122
01:03:47,480 --> 01:03:49,880
I am telling the truth, Uncle.
I am not a thief.

1123
01:03:50,000 --> 01:03:53,000
The money found in my
pocket was my hard earned money.

1124
01:03:53,240 --> 01:03:54,560
Believe me, Uncle.

1125
01:03:54,880 --> 01:03:58,080
Bhola, you think I will
believe your justification.

1126
01:03:58,360 --> 01:04:00,400
You didn't steal the money?
- Uncle.

1127
01:04:00,480 --> 01:04:04,000
When everybody said that nose-ring,
silver glasses..

1128
01:04:04,080 --> 01:04:06,160
..and other things was
robbed then what did you say?

1129
01:04:06,240 --> 01:04:10,240
Uncle, I said that you
forget to include brother's watch.

1130
01:04:10,400 --> 01:04:11,760
Exactly, Bhola.

1131
01:04:12,520 --> 01:04:14,000
If you had committed the robbery..

1132
01:04:14,080 --> 01:04:17,200
..then you would have never
reminded them of the watch.

1133
01:04:18,000 --> 01:04:22,560
Such innocent words would
never been uttered by a sinner.

1134
01:04:23,840 --> 01:04:25,560
Bhola, never.

1135
01:04:26,200 --> 01:04:28,360
Father, I don't care for others.

1136
01:04:29,000 --> 01:04:32,560
But you don't think I am a thief,
this is enough for me.

1137
01:04:33,320 --> 01:04:36,880
I couldn't tell
everybody how I earned Rs.50.

1138
01:04:37,200 --> 01:04:38,760
But I won't hide anything from you.

1139
01:04:39,000 --> 01:04:40,320
I will tell you everything.

